14:16.255 --> 14:19.925
Tiger shark!

14:19.992 --> 14:29.835
♪

14:38.077 --> 14:44.316
♪

14:44.383 --> 14:45.618
I think we lost him.

14:45.684 --> 14:47.820
That was a close one.

14:47.886 --> 14:51.023
Let's look for some customers
someplace else.

14:51.090 --> 14:54.627
<i>So the sailors found customers</i>
<i>somewhere else in the ocean.</i>

14:54.693 --> 14:59.164
Okay, that's two singles.
And for you, sir?

14:59.231 --> 15:01.000
(Chattering)

15:01.066 --> 15:03.869
A double! Certainly, sir!

15:03.936 --> 15:05.604
We need your help!

15:07.506 --> 15:09.541
Which one of these cones
is a double?

15:09.608 --> 15:11.810
Remember, double means two!

15:16.215 --> 15:17.149
{\an3}That one!

15:17.216 --> 15:18.951
That one has two scoops!

15:19.018 --> 15:23.088
Right! This ice cream cone
is a double!

15:23.155 --> 15:24.256
Here you go!

15:24.323 --> 15:25.858
(Chirping happily)

15:25.924 --> 15:28.727
And for you, sir?

15:28.794 --> 15:32.431
Tiger shark!

15:32.498 --> 15:35.234
(Whimpering)

15:35.301 --> 15:40.439
{\an3}(Sobbing)

15:41.640 --> 15:43.242
What's wrong, sir?

15:43.309 --> 15:44.977
Yeah, why are you crying?

15:45.044 --> 15:48.914
{\an5}(Whimpering)

15:45.044 --> 15:48.914
I just want some ice cream too.

15:48.981 --> 15:52.017
But you keep going away!

15:52.084 --> 15:53.352
We're sorry.

15:53.419 --> 15:55.287
We're happy to get you
some ice cream.

15:55.354 --> 15:56.889
(Chuckling happily)

15:56.955 --> 16:00.092
<i>And so the submarine sailors</i>
<i>gave the tiger shark</i>

16:00.159 --> 16:01.560
<i>some delicious ice cream.</i>

16:01.627 --> 16:05.297
One single vanilla fish!
Open wide, please.

16:06.965 --> 16:09.668
Mama mia!

16:09.735 --> 16:11.537
(Giggling)

